post_text:
We recently received notice from the Illinois State Board of Education that they are extending waivers for Summer Meals Programs through the end of this calendar year. This means:

From September 1, 2020, through December 31, 2020, hot lunches for all K-8 students will be free of charge. This includes the salad bar.

Student accounts were charged for hot lunches purchased on the first day of school, August 31. August 31 was not included in the waiver period.

Our junior high students may still purchase ala carte, but their account will be charged for the ala carte purchase. The ala carte cost is $1.50.

Students may also purchase an extra milk with their lunch, but their account will be charged. The milk cost is 35‚Çµ.

Morning recess milk/juice for our PreK-4th grade students is not covered under the waiver, so families will still be charged for their child‚Äôs morning drink.

We are excited to be able to offer this program for our families. If you have any questions, feel free to call the school office at 523-4253 or email rbecker@germantownbulldogs.org.

post_text:
Attention all GES families. The on-line student registration portal is now open. To register:

1. Go to https://www.teacherease.com/common/login.aspx
2. Log in using your email address and password.
3. If you forgot your password, click 'Forgot password' and follow prompts to reset password.
4. Once you log in, you should automatically be prompted to go through the registration process.

Registration fees can be paid on-line or in person. The office is closed the remainder of this week for floor cleaning, so making payments in person will have to wait until next week. We apologize for the inconvenience.

If you have any questions or need assistance of any type, please call the school office at 523-4253. We are here to answer your questions.

Thank you for being patient and working with us as we roll out the on-line student registration process.

post_text:
Summer is a very busy time for schools. It is typically when big projects are scheduled, such as the repaving of the parking lot/playground project we currently have under way. The existing asphalt on the west end of the parking lot has been excavated, a new rock base has been installed, and the concrete is being poured.

Upon completion of this project, our students will have a much safer surface on which to play, and visitors to the building will be able to park on the lot without worrying about tripping on an uneven surface or cracked asphalt.

The school district received a maintenance grant to assist with the funding of this project. The parish is also making a financial contribution.

We are excited for this opportunity to continue making improvements to the building and grounds.

post_text:
Kevin Wilburn asked us to share the following message with our families:

"Due to the Covid-19 pandemic and the guidelines/restrictions outlined in the Restore Illinois plan, the Mid-County Youth Baseball/Softball League (MCYL) coordinators voted unanimously to CANCEL the 2020 season. League Coordinator, Galen Mahle of the Clinton County YMCA, stated that the league waited as long as possible to make this decision, in hopes that we could salvage part of a season. However, new restrictions would have made it impossible to start practices or games until the State moves into Phase 4 of the plan, which isn't projected until close to the end of June. We want to thank all of the communities and participants for bearing with us while we worked towards a decision. We look forward to the 2021 season so that the children of Clinton County can once again "Play Ball"." Details to follow concerning uniform drop off and refund pickup.

League Coordinator, Galen Mahle of the Clinton County YMCA, stated that the league waited as long as possible to make this decision, in hopes that we could salvage part of a season. However, new restrictions would have made it impossible to start practices or games until the State moves into Phase 4 of the plan, which isn't projected until close to the end of June. post_text: Diane Schniers joined our Bulldog Team during the 2014-15 school year. Today, she will be making lunches for the last time as she is 'retiring' upon the conclusion of this school year. She comes to school every day with a positive attitude and a smile on her face. She is a team player who is willing to help out in any capacity needed. Diane was instrumental in getting our salad bar up and running. She is most definitely going to be missed. Thank you for your years of service, Diane. You have touched the lives of many and have made a difference at GES. #OnceABulldogAlwaysABulldog

Just a reminder that the deadline to order prepackaged school supplies through School Tool Box for the 2020-21 school year is quickly approaching. To place your order, simply:

1. Go to www.schooltoolbox.com.
2. Find the ‚ÄòShop for prepackaged supplies‚Äô box on the right-hand side of the page and type in Germantown 62245 in the search box.
3. Click on Germantown Elementary, and it will take you to our store.
4. When you click on the blue ‚ÄòView and Purchase‚Äô button under each tool box, it will take you a page that outlines the ‚ÄòRequired Items‚Äô that are included in the box and ‚ÄòAdd-on Items‚Äô that you can order separately if you choose.

Orders can be placed through May 31. The kits will be available for pick-up at student registration on Thursday, July 23.

Junior high parents will have to purchase the Samsill Duo 2-in-1 Document and File Organizer separately. It is available at Amazon.

Please note that this is a service we are providing our families. It is not a fundraiser. Participation is optional.

This morning, all 3 major St. Louis news stations indicated there is a good chance of light rain late this afternoon and early evening. After consulting with the 8th grade families, we have decided to reschedule the parade for this Thursday, May 21, at 7:00 p.m., when the weather is forecast to be nicer.

We hope you understand that this decision was made in the best interests of our graduates and their families. We are sorry for any inconvenience this may case.

Please help us spread the word.

We look forward to watching you spread your wings as you make your way to high school. Never forget, once a Bulldog always a Bulldog.

We would like to thank Unforgettable Photography by Anna for once again serving as a Gold Sponsor for this year's Bulldog Dash. Unforgettable Photography by Anna is not your ordinary photography studio. It is the place to go for bold, creative, and different portraits. Using their 3000 sq. feet of space, their goal is to make every session unique. At Unforgettable Photography by Anna, they take pride in developing trusting, loyal relationships. Call 618-523-9919 to contact the good folks at Unforgettable Photography by Anna.

Please consider supporting the local businesses that back our community school.

If you live in the Germantown Elementary School boundaries, have a child that will be 5 years old by September 1, 2020, and this child did NOT attend the Germantown Elementary School Pre-K Program, please email rbecker@germantownbulldogs.org or call 523-4253, so we can get your family added to the list to receive a registration packet.

We already have contact information for families with children that attended our PreK Program, so there is no need for these families to reach out to us.

Registration packets will be delivered in the next week.

There are only 3 days left to register for the 16th Annual Virtual Bulldog Dash and guarantee a collector's edition event t-shirt. The deadline is Monday, April 27. Simply click the link to register: http://tinyurl.com/bulldogdash2020. If you do not have a PayPal account, payment can be dropped off at the school office between 8:00-5:00 every weekday or mailed to 401 Walnut Street, POX Box 400, Germantown, IL, 62245.

Don't miss out on the opportunity to participate in this race at your pace on your own course when it works best with your schedule anytime between May 16-23.

By doing so you will be supporting the children of Germantown Elementary School.

If you guessed Mrs. Ski for the Friday Masked Staffer, you were correct.

Clue #1: Chuck E. Cheese, ‚ÄúWhere a kid can be a kid!‚Äù I still love to play games and listen to jokes. I love to laugh.
Clue #2: I love to play any type of sport and I am very competitive. I played college soccer.
Clue #3: Just like Chuck E. Cheese, I love to sing and dance! You can usually find me dancing in my classroom to a GoNoodle. I have also been known to guest star in some Tik Tok dances. I also love to sing, but I am not very good. Rap is more my style.
Clue #4: Chuck E. Cheese loves pizza üçï. Who doesn‚Äôt?! I love any kind of pizza. My favorite place to eat pizza is in the cafeteria with all of my students. I eat lunch with my students at least once a week.
Clue #5: Chuck E. Cheese is a mouse üê≠ and mice have horrible eye sight. I wear contacts most days, but sometimes I wear glasses.

If you guessed Mrs. Garren for the Tuesday Masked Staffer, you were correct.

Clue #1: As a teenager, I loved to read comic books, especially the ones with the driest, wittiest humor. I loved Wolverine, Iron Man, and Hulk.
Clue #2: At Murray State, I majored in Psychology and had almost enough hours for a double major in Literature.
Clue #3: I am from Kentucky. ‚ÄúCollege basketball‚Äù means University of Kentucky Wildcats.
Clue #4: I love boho, hippie, flower power styles...my daughter says, ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt believe I love all that hippie stuff, just like you, Mom!‚Äù
Clue #5: Doodling is like meditation for me. I‚Äôve always done it, but I was scared to try to draw until I was in my 30‚Äôs. That‚Äôs when I learned you can‚Äôt compare yourself to everyone else...just look for growth in yourself

Good morning, again, Bulldog Country üòä We are happy to announce that due to popular demand we have chosen to once again sell prepackaged school supplies through School Tool Box for the 2020-21 school year. To place your order, simply:

1. Go to www.schooltoolbox.com.
2. Find the ‚ÄòShop for prepackaged supplies‚Äô box on the right-hand side of the page and type in Germantown 62245 in the search box.
3. Click on Germantown Elementary, and it will take you to our store.
4. When you click on the blue ‚ÄòView and Purchase‚Äô button under each tool box, it will take you a page that outlines the ‚ÄòRequired Items‚Äô that are included in the box and ‚ÄòAdd-on Items‚Äô that you can order separately if you choose.

Orders can be placed through May 31. The kits will be available for pick-up at student registration on Thursday, July 23.

Junior high parents will have to purchase the Samsill Duo 2-in-1 Document and File Organizer separately. It is available at Amazon.

Please note that this is a service we are providing our families. It is not a fundraiser. Participation is optional.

post_text:
Mr. Son has accepted a job as principal at Brownstown Elementary School for the 2020-21 school year, so he will not be returning to Germantown Elementary. With that being said, we have an opening for a junior high math teacher for the upcoming school year. This position entails teaching 6th and 7th grade math.

Candidates must possess a registered professional educator license with the Illinois State Board of Education and an endorsement to teach junior high math.

We are interested in all candidates whether new to the profession or experienced.

If interested, please send a cover letter, resume, and 3 letters of recommendation to 401 Walnut Street, Germantown, IL, 62245, or rbecker@germantownbulldogs.org. Applications will be accepted until the position is filled.

Please share.

ATTENTION Bulldog Country! We are excited to announce that the 16th Annual Bulldog Dash will go on, BUT due to COVID-19, it will be VIRTUAL!

What does a VIRTUAL race mean?

1. Register for the race on-line and receive a Race Event T-shirt (registration is only $10!). Must register by April 27 to guarantee a t-shirt.

2. Complete your race at your pace on your course anytime between May 16th-May 23rd, 2020.

3. Submit your participation picture and race time (optional) to Robin Becker at: rbecker@germantownbulldogs.org to be entered for attendance prizes.

There will not be any individual awards given out for this virtual race. Instead the 'award' will be knowing that you made a difference for the children of Germantown Elementary School.

Online Registration is easy with no fees! http://tinyurl.com/bulldogdash2020

Packet and shirt pick-up will be at Schoendienst Park on May 16th from 8am-11am. Drive thru only.

Children 10 and under will get a participation medal.

The Bulldog Dash committee says THANK YOU for your support during these unprecedented times!

post_text: This week at GES, we are going to shift our focus to self-care. The events that have unfolded around the world over the course of the past month or so have impacted all of our lives to one degree or another. Our daily routines have been upended, and we are working to figure out our new normal. Instead of letting the stress and anxiety of the situation consume us, let's make the most of the situation. Let's embrace the opportunity to slow down. Let's enjoy the opportunity to reconnect with our loved ones. Let's focus on the health and well-being of our families. Let's make self-care our topmost priority.

Favorite School Lunch: Salisbury Steak, Mashed Potatoes, Roll

Favorite Field Trip: Ice Skating

Favorite Subject: Social Studies

Teacher Quality You Appreciate Most: Humor

Lesson Learned at GES: No matter what, you can achieve your goals.

What You Will Miss Most about GES: Having two of the best basketball coaches, Mr. Glynn and Mrs. S.

What Makes You Most Proud to be a Bulldog: Knowing that no matter what I will always be welcome at Germantown Elementary.

Finish this sentence: I will always remember...that no matter what we would always have the whole school behind us at our biggest sporting events.

Upon graduation from GES, Olivia plans to go to Central High School.

Olivia, we are so grateful you joined our Bulldog family in 2017. Never forget, once a Bulldog always a Bulldog.

post_text:
Today is National Census Day! At a time when we are all keeping a little distance, we can still come together and participate in the 2020 Census to make sure everyone is counted.

When we take time to answer the questions, we help determine the funding of communities for the next ten years.

While it is great to see the Germantown response rate is higher than that of the state of Illinois as a whole, almost half of our families still need to participate. It only takes a few minutes to complete. Please consider doing so today.

The census can be filled out online at www.My2020census.gov or call toll-free 1-844-330-2020. You can speak to a live person safely from your home.

post_text:
The 2020 Census helps determine how much money communities receive for the critical resources that children and families will depend on for the next 10 years‚Äîbasically, an entire childhood! Resources that could be impacted include food assistance, Head Start, child care, housing support, public schools, early intervention services for children with special needs, and children‚Äôs health insurance. Knowing how many children there are and where they live is essential to getting those services and programs to them.

The 2020 Census is happening now. This year the census can be filled out online at www.My2020census.gov or call toll-free 1-844-330-2020. You can speak to a live person safely from your home.

Please help us in our efforts to account for all of our children.

We would like to thank Excel Bottling and Brewing for serving as a Gold Sponsor for the 16th Annual Bulldog Dash. Excel bottling produces flavored soda through a variety of products using cane sugar, returnable bottles through vintage bottling equipment. Their most popular soft drink, Ski, was added in 1961 and accounts for a good portion of soda produced. Besides their bottled soda, Excel offers a great lineup of fountain drinks available through a variety of restaurants. Excel Bottling and Brewing is located in Breese at 488 S. Broadway. You can get your Excel fix at the Bulldog Dash as we will have free non-alcoholic drinks for participants to enjoy after the race.

Please consider supporting the local businesses that back our community school.

post_text:
To safeguard the health and wellness of all students and staff, the State of Illinois has mandated that all schools close to students beginning Tuesday, March 17, with a projected return of Tuesday, March 31. This is a dynamic situation. We are told, the return to school date may change.

Beginning next Tuesday and continuing through the mandated closure period, the school facility will be closed for public use. All activities from March 17 through March 30 will be canceled.

We ask that parents/guardians pick up any student medications and other necessary items from the school by 7:00 p.m. next Monday.

Further details will be shared with you as they are finalized.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out. I will be available throughout the school closure and will provide updates as they become available.

This afternoon, the Clinton County School Consortium Superintendents, along with the Regional Office of Education Superintendent, Ron Daniels, met to discuss a recent briefing that took place with the Clinton County Health Department. The focus of the meeting was to examine the updated recommendations involving COVID-19 (Coronavirus). I would like to give the following assurances to GES families:

1. As of today, there are no confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Clinton County.

2. Germantown Elementary School will follow the recommendations of the Clinton County Health Department moving forward as it relates to canceling events or in the most extreme case‚Äîcanceling school. At this point, there are no additional recommendations other than using the same precautions that would be used for the prevention of any other communicable disease.

Thank you for working with us in the best interests of our students.

Germantown Elementary is in immediate need of hiring a full time substitute teacher. This position entails subbing for faculty and staff members as assigned and filling a maternity leave from mid-April to the end of the school year. The hourly rate is $15 an hour with a significant increase in pay built into the maternity leave assignment. Interested candidates must possess a substitute teaching license at a minimum. Teacher certification is preferred. Contact Robin Becker at rbecker@germantownbulldogs.org or (618)523-4253 if interested.

Please help us spread the word.

post_text:
The 16th Annual Bulldog Dash will be here before you know it. We are gearing up for another successful event. We hope you consider participating in our family friendly race this year. Registration is also available online. This year, there is no additional fee to register on-line.

All money raised through this fundraiser will be allocated to technology upgrades for the school. One of the major projects we are hoping to complete in the future includes renovating our network. This would include running new Ethernet lines, installing new switches, and replacing all old WiFi access points with new access points. With these upgrades, our infrastructure would be better equipped to handle the load and would operate more efficiently and effectively.

We look forward to seeing many racers joins us at the starting line on May 16.

post_text:
This week, Mrs. Kurtz's Kindergarten class worked hard on writing some very special letters. They chose to write letters of encouragement to Maren Poettker of Aviston who was diagnosed with Neuroblastoma. While writing the letters we talked about kind words that would boost our confidence, and make us feel good. Each student then chose what they wanted to tell Maren and wrote it in letter form to be delivered.

The students then took a walking field trip to the post office to learn about how our letter would be delivered to Maren. Once they were finished, they placed their special package in the mailbox in hopes of bringing a smile to Maren's face.

Great job, kindergarten! Way to be great leaders and spread some optimism! #GOALS
